<item>
            <title>[SPARK-7713] Use shared broadcast hadoop conf for partitioned table scan.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7713</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While debugging &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7673&quot; title=&quot;DataSourceStrategy&amp;#39;s buildPartitionedTableScan always list file status for all data files &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-7673&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-7673&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we also found that we are broadcasting a hadoop conf for every Partition (backed by a Hadoop RDD). It also causes the performance regression of compiling a query involving a large number of partitions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12830806">SPARK-7713</key>
