                            <comment id="14549097" author="srowen" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 20:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same as / similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7410&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7410&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14549121" author="yhuai" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 20:13:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. It is the same thing. I will have a fix just for SQL because we just migrated our parquet to our new API for partitioned data sources and I am worry about the performance regression for users having parquet tables with lots of partitions. Then, we can have a general purpose fix under &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7410&quot; title=&quot;Add option to avoid broadcasting configuration with newAPIHadoopFile&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-7410&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-7410&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
